            <entry xml:id="entry_axsǵiag" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d480e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>axsǵiag</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d480e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>axsgiag</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d480e72"><sense xml:id="sense_d480e73"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>самый дорогой, любимый</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>dearest, beloved</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d480e82"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>настоятельный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>urgent</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d480e91"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>важный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>important</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d480e100"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>нужный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>needed</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d480e112" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>i k’wari duwwæ axsgiagidær ka ʽdtæj, oni baminævar kodtoncæ
                            Adækezæmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>двух лучших из группы послали для переговоров с Адакезой</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the two best of the group were sent to negotiate with Adakeza</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            53</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d480e134">
                        <quote>jæ axsǧiag qæbūl xæsty fæmard īs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ее любимое дитя погибло на войне</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>her beloved child died in the war</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d480e149">
                        <quote>goræty mæ axsǧiag q˳yddag īs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у меня в городе очень нужное дело</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I have an important affair in town</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d480e164" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ke baǧudæncæ mæn xuzæn læqwæntæ otæ axsgiagæj?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кому понадобились подобные мне мальчики так настоятельно?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>who needs boys like me so strongly?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1956 VII
                            50</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, отглагольное образование от не сохранившегося
                    самостоятельно глагола %iaxs-%i в значении ‘ласкать’, ‘лелеять’ и пр.
                    (%iaxs-gæ-jag%i → %iaxsgiag%i), ср. др.иран. основу <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e236" xml:id="mentioned_d480e189" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>axš-</w></mentioned> в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e241" xml:id="mentioned_d480e194" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e246" xml:id="mentioned_d480e199" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āštī</w>
                        <gloss><q>мир</q></gloss></mentioned>; для развития значения ср. хотя бы
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e254" xml:id="mentioned_d480e207" xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w/>
                        <gloss><q>Friede</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e262" xml:id="mentioned_d480e215" xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>Freund</q></gloss></mentioned>. Эту же основу мы готовы усмотреть
                    в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/> ‘гнездо’, а закономерный ее вариант
                    %iaz-%i (%i*axš-%i из %i*ag-s-%i) —- в д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/>
                    ‘давать приют’, ‘ласкать’ и в д. %iastʼonæ%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>] (из %iaz-donæ%i) ‘гнездо’; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Probable deverbal derivation from a verb %iaxs-%i, not preserved
                    independently, with the meaning ‘caress’, ‘cherish’, etc. (%iaxs-gæ-jag%i →
                    %iaxsgiag%i), cf. Old Iranian stem <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e189" xml:id="mentioned_d480e236" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>axš-</w></mentioned> in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e194" xml:id="mentioned_d480e241" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e199" xml:id="mentioned_d480e246" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āštī</w>
                        <gloss><q>peace</q></gloss></mentioned>; for the development of meaning cf.
                    at least <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e207" xml:id="mentioned_d480e254" xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w/>
                        <gloss><q>Friede</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d480e215" xml:id="mentioned_d480e262" xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>Freund</q></gloss></mentioned>. We are ready to see the same base
                    in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/> ‘nest’ and its natural variant
                    %iaz-%i (%i*axš-%i из %i*ag-s-%i) in Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/>
                    ‘give shelter’, ‘caress’ in Digor %iastʼonæ%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>] (from %iaz-donæ%i) ‘nest’; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>.</etym>
